      "reasoning": "The mutation removes the __syncthreads() barrier after writing thread_max to shared_max and before the reduction loop. However, the reduction loop itself begins with a __syncthreads() inside its first iteration (when s = blockDim.x/2, threads with tid < s execute the fmaxf and then all threads hit __syncthreads()). This first __syncthreads() in the reduction loop ensures that all threads have completed writing to shared_max before any thread reads a value written by another thread. Therefore, the removed barrier is redundant — the subsequent barrier in the reduction loop provides the necessary synchronization. The fixed shape (16x16384) with 256 threads per block means the reduction loop always executes at least one iteration, so the missing barrier never causes a race condition. Layer 2's 100+ random and stress tests confirm bitwise identical results, and no value-level input can expose a timing difference because the synchronization is still correctly enforced by the remaining barriers.",
